Rating: 4
Fantastic! Boiling takes a lot of flavor out of the meat. For ultimately tender ribs (needs time but no fuss): Precut the ribs and put them in a casserole dish. They don't have to be in a single layer. Pour the marinade on top and turned the ribs to coat. Cover tightly with aluminum foil and cook at 350F for 3 hours. They are great as is - or for a crunchier coating - after baking, broil the ribs in a single layer on a rack over a roasting pan or cookie sheet with a layer of water for just a few minutes. You can do the baking part ahead of time. Bring the ribs out a couple hours before you serve them and stick them in the broiler at the last minute!

